#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.114"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.114:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.114:0.2"
msgid "12. Lokakāmaguṇavagga "
msgstr "12. The World and the Kinds of Sensual Stimulation "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.114:0.3"
msgid "114. Paṭhamamārapāsasutta "
msgstr "114. Māra’s Snare (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.114:1.1"
msgid "“Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.114:1.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati—"
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them, "

#. VAR: vasaṃ gato → vasagato (bj-a, s-a)
msgctxt "sn35.114:1.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āvāsagato mārassa, mārassa vasaṃ gato, paṭimukkassa mārapāso. "
msgstr "they’re called a mendicant trapped in Māra’s lair, fallen under Māra’s sway, and caught in Māra’s snare. "

msgctxt "sn35.114:1.4"
msgid "Baddho so mārabandhanena yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe …. "
msgstr "They’re bound by Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.114:2.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches … "

msgctxt "sn35.114:2.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.114:2.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āvāsagato mārassa, mārassa vasaṃ gato, paṭimukkassa mārapāso. Baddho so mārabandhanena … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.92, sc3
msgctxt "sn35.114:3.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.114:3.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati—"
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keep clinging to them, "

msgctxt "sn35.114:3.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āvāsagato mārassa, mārassa vasaṃ gato, paṭimukkassa mārapāso. "
msgstr "they’re called a mendicant trapped in Māra’s lair, fallen under Māra’s sway, and caught in Māra’s snare. "

msgctxt "sn35.114:3.4"
msgid "Baddho so mārabandhanena yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe … "
msgstr "They’re bound by Māra, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.114:4.1"
msgid "Santi ca kho, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.114:4.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati—"
msgstr "If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, "

msgctxt "sn35.114:4.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu nāvāsagato mārassa, na mārassa vasaṃ gato, ummukkassa mārapāso. "
msgstr "they’re called a mendicant not trapped in Māra’s lair, not fallen under Māra’s sway, and released from Māra’s snare. "

msgctxt "sn35.114:4.4"
msgid "Mutto so mārabandhanena na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe …. "
msgstr "They’re free from Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One cannot do what he wants with them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.114:5.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches … "

msgctxt "sn35.114:5.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.114:5.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu nāvāsagato mārassa, na mārassa vasaṃ gato, ummukkassa mārapāso. Mutto so mārabandhanena na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.114:6.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.114:6.2"
msgid "Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati—"
msgstr "If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, "

msgctxt "sn35.114:6.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu nāvāsagato mārassa, na mārassa vasaṃ gato, ummukkassa mārapāso. "
msgstr "they’re called a mendicant not trapped in Māra’s lair, not fallen under Māra’s sway, and released from Māra’s snare. "

msgctxt "sn35.114:6.4"
msgid "Mutto so mārabandhanena na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato”ti. "
msgstr "They’re free from Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One cannot do what he wants with them.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.114:6.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

